article.description: Patrick Tape registered 16 points as Columbia beat Yale 83-75 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Tape scores 16 to lead Columbia past Yale 83-75
article.linkText: Tape scores 16 to lead Columbia past Yale 83-75
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Patrick Tape registered 16 points as Columbia beat Yale 83-75 on Saturday night. Quinton Adlesh had 19 points and six assists for Columbia (9-17, 4-8 Ivy League). Randy Brumant added 12 points. Gabe Stefanini had nine rebounds for the visitors. Blake Reynolds had 19 points for the Bulldogs (19-6, 9-3). Alex Copeland added 15 points. Miye Oni had 12 points. The Lions leveled the season series against the Bulldogs with the win. Yale defeated Columbia 70-64 on Feb. 15. Columbia matches up against Dartmouth at home on Friday. Yale plays Penn on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
